All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AssetInputStreamFactory
    A factory that creates input streams for asset files.
    CertificateChecker
    This class contains methods that checks whether the signature of the application is the expected signature.
    CertificateCheckerReport
    The class contains fields/method to handle threat info provided by the CertificateChecker in runtime library.
    DebugBlocker
    This class provides a method to block native debuggers.
    DebugBlocker.OnAttackListener
    Interface to implement overriding its method onAttack() and passing on an object of the implementing class to the debugger blocking API, i.e., blockDebugger().
    DebugDetector
    This class provides a set of static methods enabling the detection of various debug related application states.
    DebugDetectorReport
    The class contains fields/method to handle threat info provided by the DebugDetector in runtime library.
    DexGuardServiceIdentifier
    This class is used to identify whether the current process corresponds to the DexGuard root detection service
    EmulatorDetector
    The EmulatorDetector class bundles various emulator detection techniques.
    EmulatorDetectorReport
    The class contains fields/method to handle threat info provided by the EmulatorDetector in runtime library.
    EncryptedCordovaWebViewClient Deprecated.
    EncryptedCordovaWebViewClient should only be used with old Cordova releases (< Cordova 4.0).
    EncryptedSystemWebViewClient
    This Cordova SystemWebViewClient can decrypt assets on the fly.
    EncryptedWebViewClient
    This web view client can decrypt assets on the fly.
    EncryptedXWalkCordovaResourceClient
    This XWalkCordovaResourceClient can decrypt assets on the fly.
    FileChecker
    This class contains methods that check whether files have been modified after DexGuard has packaged them.
    FileCheckerReport
    The class contains fields/method to handle threat info provided by the FileChecker in runtime library.
    HookDetector
    This class contains a utility method to detect hooks in the runtime environment of the application, with frameworks like Frida.
    HookDetectorReport
    The class contains fields/method to handle threat info provided by the HookDetector in runtime library.
    PublicKeyTrustManager
    A trust manager that only trusts servers whose public key hashes are all in the list of trusted public key hashes.
    RootDetector
    This class detects whether the device on which it is running is rooted.
    RootDetector.Callback
    Callback to process the results of the root detection checks.
    RootDetector.InternalCallback
    Internal callback to process the results of the root detection checks.
    RootDetectorReport
    The class contains fields/method to handle threat info provided by the RootDetector in runtime library.
    RootDetectorService
    This class implements the Magisk-related checks as a service that is run in an isolated process.
    SSLPinner
    This class can pin HttpsURLConnection instances to only connect to trusted sources (e.g.
    SSLPinningEncryptedSystemWebViewClient
    The Cordova SystemWebViewClient can decrypt assets on the fly, while also pinning SSL connections to given certificates hashes.
    SSLPinningSystemWebViewClient
    This SystemWebViewClient pins SSL connections to given certificates hashes.
    SSLPinningWebViewClient
    This WebViewClient pins SSL connections to given certificates hashes.
    TamperDetector
    This class contains methods that check whether an APK has been modified after DexGuard has packaged it.
    TamperDetectorReport
    The class contains fields/method to handle threat info provided by the TamperDetector in runtime library.
    Utf8EncodingUtils  
    VirtualEnvironmentDetector
    This class contains a method to detect if the application is being run inside a virtual environment, e.g., frameworks like VirtualXposed, Parallel Box, Multiple Accounts, etc.
    VirtualEnvironmentDetectorReport
    The class contains fields/method to handle threat info provided by the VirtualEvironmentDetector in runtime library.
    WrongSSLCertificateListener
    Interface to implement when providing a callback to use when wrong certificates are detected.
